# Companion manifest — TAB-delimited: name<TAB>detect_cmd<TAB>install_cmd<TAB>kind<TAB>stacks
# Fields are separated by a SINGLE tab, NO padding spaces around fields (this is the S3 parser contract).
# Tab (not pipe) delimiter: detect_cmd may contain inner pipes (per kickoff §4 T-OCI-A).
# Companions install via THEIR official installer, detect-first, no version pin.
#
# kind=cc-plugin        → install_cmd run on consent; processed by post-install wrapper loop (setup:24-34).
# kind=external-service → routed to bridge guided-detect (setup-runtime-bridge.sh); install_cmd ignored.
# kind=mcp              → detect-first `claude mcp add`; processed by the 05-mcp layer INSIDE install.sh
#                         (before 70-deps); NEVER processed by the post-install wrapper loop (D5/I1 ordering).
#                         No version pin in install_cmd. Requires claude CLI (graceful skip if absent).
#
# stacks=* → relevant for all stacks; comma-separated list for stack-specific (e.g. react-next,ts-server).
# The stacks column is consumed by 15-companions-stack.sh for static stack-aware selection.
# The setup wrapper reads but ignores stacks (handles all companions universally).
superpowers	claude plugin list 2>/dev/null | grep -q superpowers	claude plugin install superpowers@claude-plugins-official --scope user	cc-plugin	*
runtime-bridge	curl -sf "${RUNTIME_BRIDGE_AIF_URL:-http://localhost:3009}/health"	(bridge)	external-service	*
deepwiki	claude mcp list --scope user 2>/dev/null | grep -q deepwiki	claude mcp add --scope user --transport http deepwiki https://mcp.deepwiki.com/mcp	mcp	*
